 The approval was announced in a statement in Abuja on Tuesday by the Minister of Information and Culture, Alhaji Lai Mohammed, who will chair the team. The Federal Government’s team also comprises the Attorney General of the Federation and Honourable Minister of Justice, Honourable Minister of Communications and Digital Economy, Honourable Minister of Foreign Affairs, Honourable Minister of Works and Housing, Honourable Minister of State for Labour and Employment as well as other relevant government agencies. <img loading="lazy" class="alignnone  wp-image-9902" src="https://i1.wp.com/mlpthjcvvzze.i.optimole.com/qdpMrCw.2zvi~5f0f9/w:auto/h:auto/q:90/https://i2.wp.com/ebitu.net/wp-content/uploads/2021/06/Screenshot_2021-04-11_at_3.10.45_PM-removebg-preview.png?resize=121%2C46&#038;ssl=1" alt="EBITU | #EbituBlog" width="121" height="46" data-recalc-dims="1" data-recalc-dims="1"> The post Buhari Approves FG’s Team To Engage With Twitter Team Over Suspension appeared first on E B I T U™.